         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">18/2/86. ¶  ¶ It will be encouraging to you, dear Mr Ramsay, when I tell you, that the Grand Master of Algologists, Professor Agardh found a new species of Chylocladia among your seaweeds, and describ...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="en">86.02.18</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="en">To Edward Ramsay</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="en">ML MSS.562, Letters to E. P. Ramsay 1862-91, Mitchell Library, State Library of New South Wales, Sydney.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">18/2/86.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>It will be encouraging to you, dear Mr Ramsay, when I tell you, that the Grand Master of Algologists, Professor Agardh found a new species of Chylocladia among your seaweeds, and described it as Ch. Ramsayana in the Åreskrift. Besides you discovered a new Fauchea, to which he gave the name F. nitophylloides.<note xml:id="ftn1" type="footnote" n="1">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">Both new species were described in Agardh (1873-90), part 4, pp. 46 and 39 respectively (see the bibliographical comment in n. 2, T. Ware to M, 12 June 1874 (in this edition as 74-06-12a).</p>
               </note> Much remains yet to be done for the Algology of N.SW.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>If you have even only a few of the Parrots ready,<note xml:id="ftn2" type="footnote" n="2">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <seg style="">See M to E. Ramsay, 26 March 1885, and M to E. Ramsay, 18 September 1885.</seg>
                  </p>
               </note> kindly send them over, and let me know your outlay, so that I may refund it at once by a P.O. Order.</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">Regardfully your</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Ferd. von Mueller.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="plant%20names" xml:lang="en">
               <name key="Chylocladia%20Ramsayana">Chylocladia Ramsayana</name>
            </p>
            <p rend="plant%20names" xml:lang="en">
               <name key="Fauchea%20nitophylloides">Fauchea nitophylloides</name>
            </p>
         </div>
